column5: The $300 seats ,$10 dollar beers and some of the most passionate fans have helped .....  http://www.thestar.com/sports/hockey/nhl/mapleleafs/article/1095317--maple-leafs-most-valuable-team-in-nhl-forbes?bn=1
maybe some day they'll spend that money on a real team lol....go leafs go!
maybe if they changed the name from "Leafs" to "Musky's" more people would try and catch a game from time to time...

Clearly they know how to run a profitable business, a winning team's another matter. I guess it makes sense to spend less on a team if they're still gonna fill up the seats, maybe if people weren't such die hard fans they'd be forced to spend more money lol. PS I don't even watch hockey
Just supports what I've said for years - who says you need to win in order to make money?
Having not won a cup since '67 will not hurt the leafs business model until another team takes up residence in southern Ontario and succeeds.
